@{
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Layout3.cshtml";
    ViewData["Title"] = "Deadline Status Visualisation";
}

<main class="service-page">
    <div class="service-container">
        <section class="service-hero">
            <div class="service-copy">
                <span class="service-kicker"><i class="fa-solid fa-chart-column"></i> Service Detail</span>
                <h1 class="service-title">Deadline status visualisation for faster decisions and cleaner oversight.</h1>
                <p class="service-summary">Deadline Status Visualisation gives your team a clear view of overdue and upcoming obligations in a format that is easy to scan. Instead of manually checking each record, you can assess workload, spot risk quickly, and manage priorities with far more confidence.</p>

                <div class="service-tags">
                    <span class="service-tag">Overdue and upcoming</span>
                    <span class="service-tag">Visual reports</span>
                    <span class="service-tag">Customisable filters</span>
                </div>

                <div class="service-actions">
                    <a class="service-btn service-btn-primary" href="/Contact">Request a walkthrough</a>
                    <a class="service-btn service-btn-secondary" href="/Account/Signup">Start free trial</a>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="service-visual">
                <div class="service-visual-frame">
                    <img src="~/finanza-1.0.0/img/Deadline Status & Real-Time Progress Tracking.png" alt="Deadline status visualisation dashboard" />
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="service-section">
            <div class="service-section-head">
                <span class="service-section-label">What This Service Covers</span>
                <h2>See the state of your filing workload without digging through client records one by one.</h2>
                <p>The visual dashboard is built to reduce friction during daily reviews. It shows overdue and approaching submissions clearly, helping managers and team members understand what needs attention now and what can be planned for later.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="service-split">
                <article class="service-panel">
                    <h3>How it helps</h3>
                    <p>When status visibility is poor, teams lose time moving between systems and manually interpreting due dates. A visual overview removes that friction and supports more decisive daily management.</p>
                    <p>Your practice gains a clearer picture of pressure across the entire portfolio, making it easier to balance workload, review progress, and reduce deadline risk.</p>
                </article>

                <article class="service-panel is-soft">
                    <h3>Included capabilities</h3>
                    <ul class="service-checklist">
                        <li><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i><span>Track overdue and upcoming deadlines in one view</span></li>
                        <li><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i><span>Visual reports and graphs for easier review meetings</span></li>
                        <li><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i><span>Customisable filters for firm, client, or time period</span></li>
                        <li><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i><span>Quick task assessment to support daily prioritisation</span></li>
                    </ul>
                </article>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="service-section">
            <div class="service-cards">
                <article class="service-card">
                    <span class="service-card-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-eye"></i></span>
                    <h3>At-a-glance monitoring</h3>
                    <p>Review filing status quickly without relying on fragmented lists or manual spreadsheet checks.</p>
                </article>

                <article class="service-card">
                    <span class="service-card-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-users"></i></span>
                    <h3>Better team reviews</h3>
                    <p>Use a shared visual reference during planning discussions so the whole team works from the same picture.</p>
                </article>

                <article class="service-card">
                    <span class="service-card-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-bolt"></i></span>
                    <h3>Faster decisions</h3>
                    <p>Clear visual signals make it easier to decide what to act on now, what to monitor, and what can wait.</p>
                </article>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="service-section">
            <div class="service-band">
                <div>
                    <h2>Want clearer visibility across your deadline pipeline?</h2>
                    <p>We can show you how to tailor the dashboard view to the way your firm reviews and manages obligations.</p>
                </div>
                <a class="service-btn service-btn-secondary" href="/Contact">Talk to our team</a>
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>
</main>
